WEBVTT

00:06.500 --> 00:08.991
[theme music playing]

00:28.270 --> 00:30.522
[soft rock song plays]

00:30.610 --> 00:34.068
[Courtney] What's the truth? What's true?

00:35.860 --> 00:38.067
I just think about you

00:39.870 --> 00:43.283
Got me wondering
Why we never tried again...

00:43.370 --> 00:45.668
I think we each have our own truth.

00:45.960 --> 00:47.496
So let me get this straight.

00:48.590 --> 00:49.579
[Hannah] Okay.

00:51.670 --> 00:53.046
You don't know why you're here.

00:53.420 --> 00:55.217
You don't know how I'm supposed to feel.

00:55.300 --> 00:56.961
You don't know why I haven't seen you

00:57.050 --> 00:59.427
and have tried not to think about you
for months

00:59.510 --> 01:01.808
and then you show up tonight.

01:02.890 --> 01:04.471
Precise and accurate,

01:04.980 --> 01:06.845
in true Clay Jensen style.

01:06.940 --> 01:11.388
-You're still allowed to make fun of me.
-Allowed? Obligated? Who can say?

01:12.360 --> 01:13.179
Are you real?

01:14.030 --> 01:14.849
Do you see me?

01:15.320 --> 01:16.446
Are you corporeal?

01:16.530 --> 01:18.407
_That seems like _
a scnence-flctlon question.

01:18.740 --> 01:21.072
-Can I touch you?
-That seems like a loaded question.

01:24.040 --> 01:27.032
This is fucked up, right?
[stammers] Like, I'm seriously fucked up.

01:27.710 --> 01:31.874
I don't think you're fucked up.
You're just... working through things.

01:33.000 --> 01:36.163
-Things like seeing a ghost?
-And other things.

01:38.430 --> 01:39.385
So you are a ghost.

01:40.640 --> 01:42.926
Okay, does it matter what you call me?
I'm here.

01:43.390 --> 01:46.177
-And you're here for a reason?
-I would think so.

01:47.390 --> 01:50.473
-But you don't know what it is.
-I was hoping you would.

01:51.270 --> 01:53.647
-And you're not going away.
-I don't think so.

01:53.730 --> 01:54.936
I mean, not for the moment.

01:59.360 --> 02:00.190
[scoffs]

02:01.120 --> 02:02.576
Well, that's just fucking great.

02:09.210 --> 02:11.417
-[Lainie] Clay!
-[knocking on door]

02:11.500 --> 02:12.410
Clay!

02:12.960 --> 02:14.166
You're going to be late.

02:16.670 --> 02:17.546
Shit.

02:18.800 --> 02:20.506
-Clay?
-[knocking continues]

02:20.720 --> 02:21.880
Are you all right?

02:23.810 --> 02:26.301
Uh, sorry! I'm fine.
I'm fine. I overslept.

02:28.640 --> 02:29.470
[sighs]

02:30.440 --> 02:34.763
-You slept in your clothes?
-Yeah. Homework and stuff.

02:34.860 --> 02:38.694
-But, um, everything's okay?
-Yeah, all good.

02:41.030 --> 02:42.520
How was court yesterday?

02:43.580 --> 02:44.399
[scoffs]

02:44.870 --> 02:46.110
Why don't you tell me?

02:46.330 --> 02:50.243
I was just there to drop off some files.
How about you?

02:51.040 --> 02:51.870
I was just curious.

02:53.210 --> 02:55.747
Clay, I know you said
you don't think about Hannah,

02:55.840 --> 03:00.834
that you don't care about her anymore,
but I am worried that that's not true.

03:03.680 --> 03:04.795
Gotta get dressed for school.

03:06.180 --> 03:07.010
Well...

03:07.770 --> 03:09.385
-Okay.
-Okay.

03:09.930 --> 03:10.760
Bye.

03:12.770 --> 03:16.228
-Nothing's going on?
-I have to go to school.

03:17.070 --> 03:20.278
-And you don't care about me anymore?
-Look, I tried, Hannah.

03:20.490 --> 03:22.981
I did everything I could for you,
and nothing worked.

03:23.620 --> 03:24.439
Nothing.

03:25.200 --> 03:28.112
And now you're back?
And there's still nothing I can do.

03:28.910 --> 03:30.866
If that's true, why am I here?

03:32.620 --> 03:34.121
Yeah. Exactly.

03:35.500 --> 03:36.330
[phone beeps]

03:39.840 --> 03:40.659
What the hell?

03:46.720 --> 03:48.130
Shit. I gotta go.

03:54.270 --> 03:55.089
[sighs]

04:04.860 --> 04:08.409
"Hannah wasn't the only one."
What do you suppose that means?

04:13.290 --> 04:14.279
Who gave it to you?

04:15.170 --> 04:17.661
And why now, the day my trial started?

04:20.760 --> 04:23.581
-You think they're connected?
-You think they're not?

04:24.090 --> 04:25.671
[horn honks]

04:28.010 --> 04:32.014
I think that I need to get dressed,
and go to school,

04:32.100 --> 04:33.226
and try to live my life.

04:37.900 --> 04:38.719
[sighs]

04:52.910 --> 04:54.070
[Slqe] Saddle up, partner.

04:56.710 --> 04:58.701
Did we talk about you giving me a ride?

04:58.790 --> 04:59.916
Did we have to?

05:01.340 --> 05:02.659
I mean, no, but, um...

05:04.420 --> 05:05.967
Should we talk about last night?

05:06.050 --> 05:08.211
How about instead of talking,
we just ride?

05:16.940 --> 05:18.680
[Courtney]
We all have things we keep hidden.

05:20.570 --> 05:23.277
Sometimes, keeping secrets
is how you survive.

05:23.690 --> 05:25.396
[motor rewing]

05:25.490 --> 05:27.481
[pop music playing]

05:32.330 --> 05:33.479
Because in high school,

05:34.000 --> 05:37.037
-one rumor, one picture...
-Yes.

05:37.120 --> 05:40.169
...one incident, can define you forever.

05:45.380 --> 05:46.961
You're doing the right thing, honey.

05:48.590 --> 05:49.500
I know.

05:50.550 --> 05:54.384
Now it's gonna be out there.
Everything I said in my deposition.

05:54.680 --> 05:58.684
Look, what happened to Hannah
after that photo, it happened to you, too.

05:58.770 --> 05:59.896
And that is not your fault.

06:00.150 --> 06:04.109
You told the truth. And that's all
you're gonna do again today.

06:04.650 --> 06:05.480
[phone beeps]

06:08.650 --> 06:10.311
-[Steve] Is that Mikey?
-Uh... [sighs]

06:11.200 --> 06:12.861
Aww. Todd, look.

06:12.950 --> 06:16.078
Wow. Wow, he is a keeper, huh?

06:17.160 --> 06:18.286
I guess he is.

06:19.580 --> 06:21.571
[Courtney]
And the truth doesn't even matter.

06:23.710 --> 06:24.870
Barry e-mailed me last night.

06:24.960 --> 06:27.713
He said it was Bryce's idea,
that Bryce asked you yesterday.

06:28.050 --> 06:28.869
Asked me what?

06:29.470 --> 06:31.131
If we want to use their lavwer.

06:31.430 --> 06:34.558
I'm not gonna let you take the stand
without some guidance.

06:34.640 --> 06:38.269
This kind of thing can ruin
somebody's life, even if they're innocent.

06:38.350 --> 06:41.228
I know, it's just--
we can find our own lawyer. It's fine.

06:41.310 --> 06:43.642
This is the kind of thing
your father used to handle.

06:43.980 --> 06:47.859
At times like these, we need to benefit
from our associations.

06:48.610 --> 06:50.601
[phone vibrates]

06:51.910 --> 06:53.525
-Who is it?
-It's, uh...

06:54.410 --> 06:55.900
Bryce, actually.

06:56.240 --> 06:58.492
He probably wants to get
some throws in before practice.

06:58.580 --> 07:01.367
-I should go.
-Okay, honey. And tell him thanks.

07:03.420 --> 07:05.832
-No, I wanna testify.
-[Greg] But...?

07:06.920 --> 07:08.456
[sighs] It's just...

07:10.590 --> 07:13.047
Tyler Down, who testified yesterday,

07:13.760 --> 07:15.808
called out a couple kids,
and they weren't happy.

07:16.930 --> 07:17.760
That's all.

07:19.600 --> 07:23.593
Well, if anybody gives you any flack,
you tell me, and I'll handle it.

07:24.610 --> 07:25.429
[chuckles]

07:26.190 --> 07:27.009
Thanks, Dad.

07:29.900 --> 07:33.609
[Courtney] When rumors spread,
you can fight them or ignore them,

07:33.700 --> 07:35.520
but they never really go away.

07:36.740 --> 07:38.037
When you're the target,

07:38.450 --> 07:40.782
you do anything you can
to protect yourself.

07:41.040 --> 07:43.611
[tape ripping]

07:47.590 --> 07:49.160
Jess! Hey! You wanna help?

07:49.800 --> 07:50.789
[Bryce] Babe.

07:52.840 --> 07:54.080
Where else you want 'em?

07:56.100 --> 08:00.059
[chuckles] You guys are ridiculous,
but sweet.

08:00.140 --> 08:02.597
Babe, thank you for helping me with this.

08:02.850 --> 08:03.680
Come here.

08:06.980 --> 08:08.311
[Courtney] Sometimes you hide.

08:09.730 --> 08:11.027
Sometimes you fight back.

08:14.950 --> 08:16.269
Anything you have to do.

08:19.620 --> 08:20.530
[Alex] There you go.

08:22.750 --> 08:23.739
Thank you.

08:27.000 --> 08:28.956
-Good for you. Let's go.
-[both grunt]

08:30.340 --> 08:31.329
Such a gentleman.

08:31.880 --> 08:33.928
This doesn't mean I'm gonna put out
or anything.

08:34.010 --> 08:35.921
What? Not even a handy?

08:36.010 --> 08:38.547
-Oh, my hand doesn't really work...
-All right.

08:42.100 --> 08:44.477
Hey, you know what?
Let's take the side entrance today.

08:44.560 --> 08:47.802
-But it's way further, and I get tired.
-I can carry you. Come on.

08:47.900 --> 08:49.856
Okay, you're not-- Dude, you're not--

08:49.940 --> 08:52.431
The whole reason I called you
was to avoid another scene.

08:53.240 --> 08:55.902
Getting picked up by my dad in the cop car
was embarrassing enough.

09:00.080 --> 09:02.196
[Courtney]
Because the thing is, in high school,

09:03.370 --> 09:05.156
everyone's watching you, all the time.

09:08.000 --> 09:09.376
You have to be careful.

09:20.560 --> 09:21.458
[Kevin] Get my note?

09:24.480 --> 09:27.472
About dropping by the office?
I was hoping that we could chat.

09:27.770 --> 09:31.103
-About what?
-About anything that you need.

09:31.770 --> 09:34.819
Anything I can do to help
with what you're going through.

09:35.110 --> 09:38.443
Really? You think you can be helpful
all of a sudden?

09:40.240 --> 09:41.901
Yes, uh, I think I can.

09:43.290 --> 09:47.249
Look, I know what you think about me,
you know, and about what happened,

09:48.870 --> 09:51.282
but the most important thing to me
right now, Jessica,

09:52.000 --> 09:53.160
is about keeping you safe.

09:55.380 --> 09:56.210
[girl] Jessica!

09:56.760 --> 09:59.046
Hey, where you been?
We still gotta celebrate, girl.

10:00.220 --> 10:02.552
Uh, the squad made Jess a flyer yesterday.

10:03.560 --> 10:06.552
-Wow, congratulations, Ms. Davis.
-Thank you.

10:07.520 --> 10:09.511
-Think about what I said, okay?
-Yeah.

10:12.320 --> 10:14.527
Asshole. You're welcome.

10:15.570 --> 10:16.525
Do I know you?

10:17.280 --> 10:18.315
Uh... [chuckles]

10:18.400 --> 10:21.278
Nina Jones.
And trust me, Porter's clueless.

10:21.700 --> 10:23.827
It's better to keep your mouth shut
around him.

10:29.290 --> 10:31.997
[Courtney] You have to protect yourself
any way you can.

10:32.630 --> 10:33.585
So that's what I did.

10:34.550 --> 10:37.508
-What's going on? Who are these people?
-They're all here for you.

10:38.670 --> 10:42.595
My e-mail list of concerned moms
has over a thousand names in this county.

10:42.680 --> 10:44.671
And moms do love a good craft project.

10:48.100 --> 10:50.978
That's... That's her school picture.

10:51.900 --> 10:53.470
[Jackie] Doesn't she look lovely?

10:54.690 --> 10:56.396
We're putting a face on this trial.

11:04.160 --> 11:08.039
She told me that her foundation wanted
to provide whatever support I needed.

11:08.120 --> 11:11.453
-But she didn't specify a picket line.
-No.

11:11.920 --> 11:13.876
You have to be careful, okay?

11:15.090 --> 11:19.129
These pyrotechnics can be useful,
but don't forget this is still your show.

11:20.630 --> 11:22.757
-I know that.
-And she's staying with you?

11:23.720 --> 11:25.005
Well, I have a spare room.

11:25.930 --> 11:27.841
Dennis, the house is empty. It is--

11:27.930 --> 11:30.262
There's no reason for her
to pay for a hotel room.

11:31.060 --> 11:33.472
Just... be careful.

11:35.480 --> 11:38.779
[Courtney] I spread a rumor about Hannah
and I'm not proud of it.

11:39.150 --> 11:41.983
[Dennis] And what happened
after you spread that rumor?

11:43.280 --> 11:45.487
Boys asked me and Hannah
to have sex with them.

11:46.370 --> 11:49.692
Or got physical. And they were aggressive.

11:50.120 --> 11:51.906
[scoffs] And I couldn't handle it.

11:53.290 --> 11:57.033
This was just a meaningless kiss.
All right? Girls do it all the time.

11:57.130 --> 12:00.793
And what to your direct knowledge
did the school do

12:01.590 --> 12:04.002
in response to Hannah
being sexually harassed?

12:04.090 --> 12:07.139
Or the fact that a lewd photo
of two students

12:07.220 --> 12:09.051
was being shared on campus?

12:10.770 --> 12:11.589
Nothing.

12:13.020 --> 12:14.260
The school did nothing.

12:18.770 --> 12:19.816
[Clay] Who did this?

12:22.240 --> 12:24.481
Someone I talked about yesterday,
I'm guessing.

12:27.240 --> 12:28.070
At the trial.

12:32.160 --> 12:34.116
This is what happens
when you tell the truth.

12:39.750 --> 12:40.580
Ask him.

12:42.420 --> 12:46.333
Did you just come here to look
at the destruction that is my life, or...?

12:46.760 --> 12:48.546
No. I was wondering, do you ever...

12:49.930 --> 12:51.215
work with Polaroids?

12:52.770 --> 12:54.260
Amateur hipster tripe.

12:55.770 --> 12:59.604
-I'll take that as a no.
-It's retro analog bullshit.

13:00.070 --> 13:03.187
-There's no negatives, what's the point?
-Unless that is the point.

13:03.690 --> 13:05.146
So no one can make a copy?

13:05.610 --> 13:08.943
No, you can make a copy of anything,
you just take a digital picture of it.

13:10.530 --> 13:13.579
But, yeah, you want one print
to hold on to, take a Polaroid.

13:15.580 --> 13:16.740
Do you know these people?

13:18.290 --> 13:20.087
Tommy Shuster, Erica...

13:20.710 --> 13:23.417
Charles, I think.
I shot Tommy a few times for baseball.

13:24.880 --> 13:27.007
-So they go here?
-They did.

13:27.640 --> 13:29.426
They were seniors when we were freshmen.

13:32.100 --> 13:33.556
Do you think he knew Scott Reed?

13:33.970 --> 13:36.689
Don't all those troglodytes know
each other? Why do you care?

13:40.020 --> 13:41.146
I'm not sure I do.

13:45.240 --> 13:47.390
Only have a second, coach.
I got a class waiting.

13:47.490 --> 13:48.309
What's up?

13:48.410 --> 13:52.733
Well, I understand you had a little chat
with one of my players yesterday.

13:53.660 --> 13:56.288
I'd appreciate it
if you'd come see me first next time.

13:56.370 --> 13:58.747
Okay, well, it's my job
to have a chat with students.

13:58.830 --> 14:01.879
I can't be coming to you every time
one of them happens to play baseball.

14:01.960 --> 14:02.949
No, sure, sure.

14:04.050 --> 14:06.837
Look, I'm glad we're working on awareness,

14:06.920 --> 14:10.469
and educating these kids about consent,
and everything you're doing. It's great.

14:11.510 --> 14:13.250
I'm just looking for a little teamwork.

14:14.180 --> 14:15.340
I give the right speeches,

14:16.020 --> 14:19.012
give me a heads up if you've got
a concern about one of my guys.

14:19.100 --> 14:23.639
Okay. I got a concern
about all your guys. Heads up.

14:25.070 --> 14:28.813
You know what, I'm sick of athletes
always being the targets.

14:29.200 --> 14:32.192
Coach. Athletes have the run
of this school, and you know it.

14:32.280 --> 14:34.191
I just don't want them to run kids over.

14:34.290 --> 14:36.827
You want teamwork?
Check your boys, so I don't have to.

14:40.370 --> 14:44.033
We've been talking about
how do you control your impulses.

14:44.550 --> 14:48.668
Today we're going to do an exercise
that will help you think before you act.

14:49.340 --> 14:52.138
Because you're gonna do the thinking
for someone else.

14:52.720 --> 14:55.302
You're gonna be someone else's eyes
and their ears,

14:55.890 --> 14:57.380
and guide them around the room.

14:57.850 --> 15:01.149
-Or out of a window.
-Maybe, Cyrus.

15:01.850 --> 15:04.683
[scoffs] But you'll be
switching blindfolds halfway through,

15:04.770 --> 15:06.647
so don't do anything
you don't want done to you.

15:07.860 --> 15:08.679
Okay?

15:09.650 --> 15:11.356
That means find a partner.

15:12.360 --> 15:13.611
Or I'll find one for you.

15:14.740 --> 15:17.573
You'd think they'd run these class names
by a focus group first.

15:19.080 --> 15:21.742
"Ass Class." You're a pretty good artist.

15:25.040 --> 15:27.042
Kind words from the master photographer.

15:33.180 --> 15:34.135
That was you, right?

15:35.260 --> 15:37.558
You won that photo contest
with that night vision picture

15:37.640 --> 15:38.846
of the dog pissing last year?

15:41.190 --> 15:42.088
Punk rock, dude.

15:46.770 --> 15:47.600
Should we...?

15:50.860 --> 15:51.849
Why the hell not?

15:53.820 --> 15:54.650
Kinlq.

15:55.160 --> 15:58.323
We just shared a class together.
We weren't really friends.

15:58.830 --> 16:02.709
[Sonya] But she didn't confide
in anyone else about her fears, correct?

16:03.290 --> 16:04.109
I don't think so.

16:05.170 --> 16:08.333
Not any other friends? Her parents?

16:10.210 --> 16:12.041
[Hannah]
I don't know, it could be a stalker.

16:12.130 --> 16:13.006
[Olivia] A stalker?

16:13.090 --> 16:16.799
I highly doubt that kind of thing
is going on in our neighborhood.

16:16.890 --> 16:17.845
It's a real thing.

16:17.930 --> 16:20.171
-Celebrities have Otrl11em all the time.

16:20.270 --> 16:24.183
-So we're a celebrity now?
-No. You know what I mean. Forget it.

16:24.270 --> 16:27.819
Honey, no. Hannah.
Honey, I'm sorry. All right, I just...

16:29.320 --> 16:34.019
[sighs] Look, I think that you have
a little anxiety about this new school.

16:34.110 --> 16:35.020
It's not anxiety!

16:35.450 --> 16:38.271
Okay, I heard something out there
last night. Like clicking.

16:38.370 --> 16:39.735
Well, maybe it was the wind.

16:39.830 --> 16:43.288
Yesterday, your father was saying
he thinks the raccoons are back.

16:43.370 --> 16:44.610
It's not raccoons.

16:45.250 --> 16:49.493
Honey, look,
this is the safest neighborhood

16:49.590 --> 16:51.455
that, you know, we could afford.

16:51.550 --> 16:54.041
Your father checks statistics
on this kind of thing.

16:54.550 --> 16:58.463
And I just know... I know that for me,
when I have a lot on my mind,

16:58.550 --> 17:00.131
my mind takes revenge.

17:02.520 --> 17:03.760
Yeah. You're probably right.

17:06.730 --> 17:11.349
So, finding no help from home,
she enlists you.

17:12.190 --> 17:13.930
Mom can't help, but you can?

17:15.820 --> 17:16.650
Why you?

17:17.910 --> 17:19.025
[Courtney] I don't know.

17:19.490 --> 17:23.654
But like I said, I was there.
And she was always nice to me.

17:24.200 --> 17:25.280
[Sonya] Nice to you.

17:25.370 --> 17:29.033
Defense Exhibit C, Your Honor,
as stipulated.

17:29.960 --> 17:34.374
Uh, I'm curious, Courtney, was Hannah
just being nice to you there, too?

17:39.390 --> 17:40.675
Describe what you see, please?

17:45.480 --> 17:46.595
[sighs] There's, um...

17:48.190 --> 17:51.762
more of Tyler's photos of Hannah and me,
from that night.

17:53.440 --> 17:57.979
[Sonya] Now, you said before that
it was just a meaningless kiss, correct?

17:58.490 --> 17:59.309
[Courtney] Yes.

17:59.700 --> 18:05.445
So, now how could it be meaningless
if there's more than one?

18:07.080 --> 18:10.129
Or is that not a picture of Hannah
kissing you back?

18:12.090 --> 18:14.240
[spectators murmuring]

18:17.510 --> 18:19.717
-Hey.
-Hey, where were you this morning?

18:19.800 --> 18:22.849
I was avoiding Chle.
And, like, everyone else.

18:22.930 --> 18:23.749
What's wrong?

18:25.810 --> 18:28.882
-Someone's trying to keep me quiet.
-What? What happened?

18:28.980 --> 18:30.766
Not here. Come on.

18:32.360 --> 18:34.180
[Alex] Wow, that is seriously messed up.

18:34.900 --> 18:37.391
Yeah, somebody is fucking with my head.

18:38.320 --> 18:40.697
And my head's already
plenty fucked up all on its own.

18:44.280 --> 18:46.862
Somehow I don't see Bryce
walking into a sex shop.

18:47.960 --> 18:49.154
What about Chle?

18:49.250 --> 18:52.788
I don't know, she's in smart classes
but she does stupid things.

18:52.880 --> 18:54.791
I can't see her having any ideas.

18:54.880 --> 18:56.370
-It's gotta be someone.
-Well...

18:56.880 --> 19:00.919
whoever it is, it'll stop
if you just tell the truth tomorrow.

19:01.340 --> 19:02.887
How does that make any sense?

