I have to do it in my time, in my way.

37:56.600 --> 37:57.430
Yes.

38:01.270 --> 38:02.567
I should...

38:02.650 --> 38:05.062
-No. No. No, I...
-I should go.

38:12.790 --> 38:14.439
["Woman is a Word" plays]

38:14.540 --> 38:17.998
[Courtney] Instead of facing my fears
and clearing up all the rumors,

38:18.540 --> 38:19.916
I let Hannah take the fall.

38:21.250 --> 38:24.299
I was afraid of what people might think
if they knew.

38:25.510 --> 38:28.752
I'm only an image of what you see

38:29.800 --> 38:32.928
I'm only an image of what you see

38:33.560 --> 38:37.098
I'm only an image of what you see

38:37.180 --> 38:41.059
Courtney, some people might wonder,
if you didn't tell the truth for so long,

38:41.310 --> 38:43.221
how do we know
you're telling the truth now?

38:44.320 --> 38:45.469
Because it was time.

38:46.530 --> 38:48.270
And because I owe it to Hannah.

38:50.990 --> 38:53.527
[Courtney] And I guess we all have things
we try to hide.

38:53.620 --> 38:56.441
I'm only a woman if woman is a word

38:56.540 --> 38:58.280
But they can't stay hidden forever.

38:58.370 --> 39:01.498
Bird to a bee, bird to a bee

39:04.710 --> 39:07.588
-[Jessica] That was brave.
-Sorry?

39:08.090 --> 39:11.799
I read that blog. What you did today,
at court, it was brave.

39:12.140 --> 39:14.677
-I don't know about that.
-No, It was.

39:14.810 --> 39:18.132
-You helped Hannah.
-Yeah, but I hurt her first.

39:18.310 --> 39:21.097
[stammers] I told lies about her
and I messed up her life.

39:22.690 --> 39:24.009
You weren't the only one.

39:26.690 --> 39:29.773
Did anyone threaten you
before you testified?

39:30.570 --> 39:31.400
No.

39:32.240 --> 39:34.572
Why? Did something happen to you?

39:36.580 --> 39:37.865
No, no, I...

39:41.290 --> 39:44.123
Was it hard... to tell the truth?

39:45.040 --> 39:45.870
Yes.

39:47.760 --> 39:48.579
But it was time.

39:49.550 --> 39:53.008
I'm only a woman if woman is a word

39:53.090 --> 39:54.796
Bird to a bee...

39:56.100 --> 39:57.761
[Courtney] And I think this trial...

39:57.970 --> 40:00.848
this trial is going to force
a lot of people to tell the truth.

40:03.190 --> 40:05.351
For better, or for worse.

40:30.460 --> 40:33.293
-[piano music plays softly]
-[indistinct chattering]

40:34.800 --> 40:37.507
-[Matt speaks indistinctly]
-[Skye chuckling]

40:37.600 --> 40:39.090
Not a fan of the gluten free?

40:39.180 --> 40:41.922
Uh, hello? Mom?

40:42.350 --> 40:44.978
[Matt] Hey, kiddo. Your mom's
still at work. We're in here.

40:45.350 --> 40:47.306
[Matt speaks indistinctly]

40:47.400 --> 40:50.858
It's like gluten-free pasta.
It's like moisture-free water.

40:50.940 --> 40:52.487
[Slqe and Matt chuckling]

40:52.570 --> 40:53.855
[Slqe] Sounds delicious.

40:54.160 --> 40:58.028
-[Clay] Guys, what's going on?
-We're making hand-rolled pasta.

40:58.410 --> 41:00.196
Your dad taught me. Wait, check it!

41:00.740 --> 41:01.570
[dough splatters]

41:01.660 --> 41:03.958
-[Matt] When it's done, it'll stick.
-Okay.

41:04.040 --> 41:06.702
And why are we hand-rolling pasta?

41:07.130 --> 41:09.451
Slqe said she liked Italian.
Figure it's the least we could do.

41:09.550 --> 41:10.835
It's our first dinner together.

41:10.920 --> 41:13.127
Your mom's thrilled, by the way.
Big points scored.

41:14.010 --> 41:17.639
_ -Our first dinner.
-Clay, this was your Idea, remember?

41:17.720 --> 41:22.339
-We talked about it at lunch.
-Um, yeah, that's not exactly...

41:22.810 --> 41:25.222
-Slqe, I think this might be ready.
-Yeah. Okay.

41:25.310 --> 41:26.390
You wanna try again?

41:27.560 --> 41:28.891
-Ready?
-Yeah. Try not to...

41:28.980 --> 41:30.891
-Ooh, ow. [puffs]
-Okay.

41:30.980 --> 41:32.106
-[pop51
-Hey!

41:32.190 --> 41:34.272
Oh, my God! Yes!

41:34.450 --> 41:36.520
- Bella, bella. Molto bene!
-[Skye] Totally sticks.

41:37.660 --> 41:42.108
[Mr. Down] That is graphic.
I don't know if I approve of this game.

41:42.790 --> 41:43.609
Let's go again.

41:46.080 --> 41:47.069
Dad, what is this?

41:48.500 --> 41:49.660
What? No, I wanna learn.

41:51.380 --> 41:53.416
Well, at this rate,
that's gonna take years.

41:53.710 --> 41:54.540
[scoffs]

41:54.920 --> 41:58.299
Besides, I heard you on the phone
with the school, earlier.

41:59.680 --> 42:00.499
So, what's up?

42:03.850 --> 42:06.762
Well, I was wondering
if maybe we should, um,

42:07.390 --> 42:10.689
transfer you to... another school.

42:13.570 --> 42:14.389
Really?

42:17.030 --> 42:20.989
But... how would that look for colleges?

42:21.830 --> 42:25.539
Well, I really just want to make sure
that you make it to college.

42:27.160 --> 42:30.072
But, I mean, what about my friends here?

42:31.880 --> 42:35.122
-I have Alex. He needs me, Dad.
-I know.

42:35.420 --> 42:38.423
But Alex,
he's recovering from a traumatic...

42:39.890 --> 42:42.632
and I don't know
if it's the healthiest thing for you.

42:43.260 --> 42:46.058
-So, I can't hang out with him anymore?
-No, but...

42:48.390 --> 42:51.302
Is there no one else, you know,
that you have a connection with?

42:51.860 --> 42:52.679
No, I do.

42:53.650 --> 42:56.733
Actually, yeah, no.
[stammers] I... totally forgot.

42:56.820 --> 42:59.732
Uh, Cyrus, in Mr. Porter's class.

42:59.820 --> 43:04.484
He's like an amazing artist.
And, you'd-- um, you'd like him.

43:04.580 --> 43:05.820
-That's great.
-Yeah.

43:05.910 --> 43:07.366
-Great! Bring him over.
-Cool.

43:07.450 --> 43:08.496
We'll play some vids.

43:10.210 --> 43:11.495
No one calls them that.

43:13.340 --> 43:14.204
I call them that.

43:16.260 --> 43:17.079
Okay.

43:18.510 --> 43:22.719
[Todd] All right, here we go. Yes.

43:24.720 --> 43:26.676
Desert Hearts is supposed to be a classic.

43:26.770 --> 43:29.307
The Kids Are All Right,
Blue is the Warmest Color...

43:30.730 --> 43:33.016
-Maybe we wait and watch this one last.
-Wha...

43:33.110 --> 43:35.476
Isn't this just very binary thinking?

43:35.570 --> 43:38.061
Movies and shows are a wonderful way
to open up a dialogue.

43:38.150 --> 43:41.779
So we're screening one about a man
who breaks up a lesbian couple?

43:42.360 --> 43:44.408
-Oh, God. I forgot about that part.
-Yeah.

43:44.740 --> 43:47.117
At_ least the lesbians
aren't serial killers or policewomen.

43:47.200 --> 43:50.203
And the male gaze makes
Blue is the Warmest Color very suspect

43:50.290 --> 43:52.076
as fodder for positive conversation.

43:52.170 --> 43:56.163
Good Lord, you overanalyze everything.
Probably why she didn't tell us before.

43:58.300 --> 44:01.212
-Are you saying that it is my fault?
-It's nobody's fault.

44:04.180 --> 44:07.889
-Or it's my fault.
-Oh, no, no, no. No.

44:08.390 --> 44:12.383
-Honey, honey. Aww. Hey, sweetie--
-[sobbing]

44:13.150 --> 44:15.550
Everyone takes the time they take.

44:17.520 --> 44:18.771
[Steve] Why are you crying?

44:20.150 --> 44:21.777
[sniffles] It's nothing, it's...

44:24.990 --> 44:26.696
[sighs] You're just amazing, and...

44:28.370 --> 44:30.361
-I'm so luclq to have you both.
-Oh.

44:33.540 --> 44:35.201
Come on. Come here.

44:39.340 --> 44:40.659
[whispers] We love you.

44:41.470 --> 44:43.927
[Courtney]
The truth can free you if you let it.

44:44.260 --> 44:46.592
[Lainie] So it's graffiti?

44:47.390 --> 44:50.598
It's a... It's a mural, Mom.
It's called street art.

44:50.810 --> 44:53.688
It's very popular.
It's one of the oldest art forms.

44:53.770 --> 44:56.682
If you think about it,
cave paintings were street art.

44:56.770 --> 44:59.853
-Yeah. Yes.
-That's-- Thank you, Dad.

45:00.610 --> 45:04.853
And, um, how long have you two
been making this art?

45:05.240 --> 45:06.446
-Couple months.
-Not long.

45:06.530 --> 45:09.442
Months! This must be some mural.
[chuckles]

45:09.830 --> 45:13.368
-Well, we don't always paint.
-No?

45:14.160 --> 45:16.822
You don't? You're gone for hours, Clay.
What else are you doing?

45:16.920 --> 45:20.412
-Yeah, what else do we do, Clay?
-We, um...

45:21.000 --> 45:24.504
-We hang out. Mostly.
-What does that mean?

45:24.590 --> 45:27.844
I never know. Is that slang for sex?

45:28.100 --> 45:29.840
-Mom!
-That's "hook up," honey.

45:29.930 --> 45:30.999
Hook up, yes.

45:31.100 --> 45:36.049
Well, if you two are, um, hooking up...
I just hope you're being careful.

45:36.900 --> 45:43.237
We, uh... aren't. Hooking up, I mean.
We're, uh... So... all good.

45:43.320 --> 45:45.026
-Yep.
-Okay.

45:46.240 --> 45:49.528
Um... should we-- can we be excused?

45:49.990 --> 45:51.821
What's gotten into you?
We're in the middle of dinner.

45:52.370 --> 45:54.656
-Nothing, I'm just full.
-Yeah.

45:54.750 --> 45:58.163
This pasta is filling.
Yeah, it was so good, though.

45:58.250 --> 46:00.411
-So good.
-So thank you, guys. Appreciate it.

46:01.000 --> 46:03.298
-Yeah. Thank you.
-Thanks for dinner, guys.

46:05.590 --> 46:07.217
-Bye.
-You guys are the best. Thanks.

46:11.310 --> 46:12.504
Jesus, what is your--?

46:15.020 --> 46:15.839
Holy shit.

46:29.070 --> 46:31.026
[indistinct chattering]

46:31.120 --> 46:32.405
[man] Don't forget to breathe.

46:32.990 --> 46:34.867
-I am breathing.
-You're not, so much.

46:38.580 --> 46:40.207
[grunts]

46:41.670 --> 46:42.489
Wow.

46:43.050 --> 46:46.258
That's some hard hits today.
You got something on your mind?

46:46.670 --> 46:49.924
[pants] Nah, I don't. I just need you...

46:51.300 --> 46:54.383
to sign this form
for my probation officer.

46:54.470 --> 46:55.596
Right on.

46:56.390 --> 46:58.802
Six more sessions left. Not bad.

46:59.440 --> 47:02.147
Think your anger's been adequately
managed in our time together?

47:02.560 --> 47:04.528
Huh. I'll let you know.

47:06.110 --> 47:08.692
We gotta get in the ring
before you're done. You and me.

47:09.360 --> 47:13.148
Uh... I don't think so. But thank you.

47:16.160 --> 47:19.459
She washes one dress
and it sets me back five months.

47:20.080 --> 47:23.038
I swear, I was ready to kick her out
right then and there.

47:26.340 --> 47:31.209
But I think she might be a friend,
and I don't have many of those right now.

47:33.760 --> 47:36.137
-Present company excluded.
-No, I get it.

47:37.020 --> 47:38.510
Friends who aren't in high school.

47:38.600 --> 47:39.419
[chuckles]

47:42.560 --> 47:43.470
You know, Andy...

47:45.110 --> 47:48.147
Andy used to tell me, when I'd listen
to the tapes for the umpteenth time,

47:48.240 --> 47:52.654
and I would call you with new questions,
he would say how inappropriate it was

47:52.740 --> 47:54.310
that I was spending time with you.

47:54.620 --> 47:57.828
Really? You didn't tell him
that I don't play for your team?

47:59.250 --> 48:01.206
What happened to that boyfriend of yours?

48:01.290 --> 48:04.077
The handsome guy?
I haven't seen him around in weeks.

48:05.500 --> 48:07.206
-Brad.
-Brad.

48:10.010 --> 48:11.045
Yeah, we broke up.

48:12.430 --> 48:14.079
Oh. That's too bad.

48:16.310 --> 48:18.517
-He was pretty.
-Yeah.

48:18.600 --> 48:20.761
He didn't talk much,
but he was very pretty.

48:22.600 --> 48:23.430
What happened?

48:25.190 --> 48:26.100
Um...

48:27.190 --> 48:29.317
He didn't want to date a kid anymore.

48:31.360 --> 48:34.659
Wanted bigger things.
He was tired of the high school bullshit.

48:35.070 --> 48:37.652
Here I am, bringing you more
high school bullshit, huh?

48:37.740 --> 48:41.494
No, never. I'm here for you, always.

48:46.380 --> 48:48.792
God, I sit in that courtroom, Tony,

48:51.340 --> 48:53.422
and I feel like I never knew my daughter.

48:55.840 --> 49:01.176
She kept all these... secrets.
Why did she have so many secrets?

49:03.600 --> 49:04.680
I think, uh...

49:06.770 --> 49:10.524
I think, sometimes, we aren't keeping
secrets to hide from other people.

49:12.280 --> 49:15.852
I think, sometimes, we're keeping them
to protect those people.

49:16.320 --> 49:18.527
[soft rock song plays]

49:21.870 --> 49:23.201
-[Skye] What's wrong?
-[Clay] Nothing.

49:27.540 --> 49:30.293
-Okay, just stop.
-Wait, I...

49:30.380 --> 49:31.620
Stop. Just...

49:39.470 --> 49:44.305
-Are you ashamed of me?
-What? Slqe, no. I...

49:44.770 --> 49:47.227
Then what the fuck is going on here, Clay?

49:48.060 --> 49:51.268
I mean, why didn't your parents
know about me?

49:52.190 --> 49:57.776
Because they're my parents. They meddle.
Honestly, it has nothing to do with you.

49:57.860 --> 49:59.316
-Rea|ly?
-Yeah.

49:59.950 --> 50:02.783
It doesn't have to do with the way I look?

50:02.870 --> 50:06.112
Or that I have,
like, tattoos and piercings

50:06.210 --> 50:07.859
and, like, cuts all over?

50:07.960 --> 50:10.872
Jesus, Slqe, no.
I don't care about that stuff.

50:10.960 --> 50:11.790
You know that.

50:12.800 --> 50:17.089
-You don't care. Of course.
-WaIt...

50:18.590 --> 50:20.546
Slqe, hang on. Let's just--

50:21.140 --> 50:22.596
That's not what I meant, okay?

50:22.680 --> 50:26.559
What I mean is, I like the way you look.
I like you.

50:26.890 --> 50:30.018
Really? Because your body
is kinda saying the opposite.

50:30.650 --> 50:32.436
Maybe my head's still scrambled

50:32.520 --> 50:34.522
from you trying to jerk me off
in front of my parents.

50:34.610 --> 50:35.850
Well, I'm sorry!

50:36.190 --> 50:39.489
I'm sorry for trying to be
fucking spontaneous!

50:39.570 --> 50:42.733
You could've talked to me, you didn't have
to just show up at my house.

50:43.450 --> 50:44.360
It was weird!

50:44.450 --> 50:48.864
I'll tell you what's weird: you still
being in love with a fucking dead girl.

50:51.000 --> 50:51.830
Don't...

50:52.090 --> 50:55.708
-Don't say that, please. That's not true.
-Rea|ly?

50:56.670 --> 51:00.299
You freaked out at our spot last night
the day that her case is going to trial.

51:00.390 --> 51:04.133
Then you freaked out at lunch today
because I brought up you going to court.

51:04.220 --> 51:08.008
It's like, wherever we go, she's there!

51:08.480 --> 51:09.629
No. That's not...

51:10.940 --> 51:11.759
thatsinsane.

51:12.190 --> 51:13.225
[Slqe and Hannah] Is it?

51:13.610 --> 51:17.489
It's all about Hannah, Clay,
and it always will be.

51:17.940 --> 51:23.446
How am I supposed to compete with that?
She's perfect. And she's dead.

51:23.530 --> 51:27.159
-Really, Slqe. Can we sit and talk?
-I don't wanna fucking sit down!

51:28.960 --> 51:31.531
Tell me I'm wrong. Tell me you love me.

51:33.040 --> 51:35.201
Tell me you're over her, then.

51:35.630 --> 51:38.667
I... I love you. I...

51:39.260 --> 51:40.079
And?

51:42.590 --> 51:44.842
And you're over me.
Clay, it's okay, just say it.

51:50.560 --> 51:52.266
-Clay?
-I can't!

51:56.190 --> 51:59.353
[sighs] I'm sorry, but I can't say that.

52:01.860 --> 52:05.193
You have been lying to me,

52:05.280 --> 52:07.111
you fucking liar!

52:07.200 --> 52:10.112
Slqe! Skye! Shit.

52:10.540 --> 52:11.825
Slqe!

52:12.920 --> 52:14.035
Slqe.

52:22.010 --> 52:23.750
-[bike starting]
-Slqe.

52:24.010 --> 52:26.501
[motor rewing]

52:27.720 --> 52:28.596
Fuck.

52:31.770 --> 52:35.103
-[Hannah] What are you gonna do?
-I'm gonna go after her.

52:35.440 --> 52:39.479
-You sure that's a good idea?
-No. I think it's a terrible idea.

52:39.570 --> 52:42.733
But a worse idea is staying here
and discussing it all with you, so...

52:43.700 --> 52:46.271
You think that's what she wants,
for you to chase her?

52:46.530 --> 52:49.693
Are you serious right now?
Are you fucking serious?

52:51.330 --> 52:52.786
"Part of me was saying, 'Don't go."'

52:53.290 --> 52:56.453
Remember that, Hannah?
Your words. My tape.

52:56.790 --> 52:59.202
-"Part of me was saying, 'Don't go."'
-I remember.

52:59.300 --> 53:01.416
Well, there you go.

53:02.760 --> 53:04.170
She's not me, Clay.

53:05.640 --> 53:06.459
No.

53:07.140 --> 53:07.959
No one is.

53:10.430 --> 53:14.639
I think it projects strength
and confidence, don't you?

53:16.770 --> 53:18.681
Maybe we can pull your hair back a little?

53:19.820 --> 53:20.718
Something like this?

53:21.740 --> 53:24.140
Sure, Mom. Whatever you think.

53:28.330 --> 53:30.195
[mother]
Want to sleep in your own bed tonight?

53:31.080 --> 53:33.492
-You must be getting tired of our floor.
-No.

53:35.080 --> 53:35.910
No, I'm not.

53:39.000 --> 53:39.830
Okay.

53:42.550 --> 53:45.622
[Courtney] Or fear of the truth
can keep you trapped in your secrets.

53:46.640 --> 53:51.259
[Sonya] In discovery, the plaintiffs found
that your date book was missing a page,

53:52.520 --> 53:54.135
which seems to be the page

53:54.230 --> 53:56.801
from the last date
of your meeting with Hannah.

53:58.190 --> 54:00.101
-Hmm.
-I'm not gonna ask you

54:00.190 --> 54:03.023
why that page is missing.
Not now, not in court. But they will.

54:05.530 --> 54:09.773
Well, I heard you made Courtney Crimsen
come out on the stand today.

54:09.870 --> 54:12.532
That's... that's messed up.

54:12.700 --> 54:14.327
I didn't make her do anything.

54:16.210 --> 54:18.201
I just asked the questions I had to ask.

54:18.920 --> 54:23.209
They're kids. They're children.

54:24.590 --> 54:25.966
They knew what they were doing.

54:27.930 --> 54:28.749
Did you?

54:39.560 --> 54:41.721
[Courtney]
And someone who's keeping a secret...

54:45.030 --> 54:48.522
who's desperate to keep that secret,
and desperate to stay hidden...

54:52.410 --> 54:54.071
can hurt everyone around them.

55:07.260 --> 55:10.582
There will always come a time
when we're forced to face the thing

55:10.680 --> 55:11.886
we're most afraid of.

55:11.970 --> 55:13.210
No, no, no. No.

55:15.140 --> 55:15.959
Slqe!

55:16.270 --> 55:19.342
Slqe! Wait, Mrs. Miller! What is she--

55:19.440 --> 55:21.852
-What happened?
-Nothing that hasn't happened before.

55:22.310 --> 55:25.609
-I didn't mean to upset her.
-She's not upset. She's ill.

55:25.690 --> 55:27.601
Please, just... just go home.

55:28.740 --> 55:30.196
[ambulance honks]

55:30.530 --> 55:32.657
[siren wailing]

55:46.590 --> 55:50.549
You really do have a thing
for complicated girls.

56:08.650 --> 56:09.730
[screaming]

56:09.820 --> 56:11.390
["Burning House Of Love" playing]

56:18.950 --> 56:20.827
[Katherine Langford]
For help finding crisis resources,

56:20.910 --> 56:22.992
visit 13reasonswhy.info.

56:23.080 --> 56:26.129
Drive by my house late at night

56:26.210 --> 56:29.293
You can see from the freeway above

56:29.960 --> 56:33.259
No silhouette, but a light left on

56:33.470 --> 56:35.961
Burning there for love

56:36.810 --> 56:39.461
Burning there for love

56:41.680 --> 56:44.934
Smoke is rising from the fire

56:45.310 --> 56:48.063
Coming out my back door

56:48.480 --> 56:51.438
I'm inside, sound asleep

56:51.950 --> 56:54.566
Cigarette on the floor

56:55.490 --> 56:57.947
Burning there for love

56:58.870 --> 57:04.035
Burning there for love

57:06.710 --> 57:10.043
Well, I can still remember

57:10.510 --> 57:12.876
A couple of years ago

57:13.550 --> 57:17.008
When the smoke and flame
From our names

57:17.100 --> 57:19.967
Was a burning house of love

57:20.560 --> 57:23.438
Yeah, a burning house of love

57:24.140 --> 57:28.895
A burning house of love

